com.chrismin13.additionsapi.items

Class StorageCustomItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.chrismin13.additionsapi.items.StorageCustomItem

  • public class StorageCustomItem
extends Object
    Used for Converting the Objects saved in the data.yml file. Meant mostly for internal use in the API. In order to obtain one, use the methods is DataFile
    Author:
    chrismin13

                         short durability,
                         String idName,
                         String texture)
        Create a new StorageCustomItem. This is just a Java Object and won't be saved to the Data.yml file. For that, use the methods at DataFile.
        Parameters:
        material - The Material of the StorageCustomItem.
        durability - The Durability Value of the StorageCustomItem
        idName - The ID Name of the StorageCustomItem
        texture - The Texture Name of the StorageCustomItem

      • getDurability

        public short getDurability()
        Returns:
        The StorageCustomItem's Durability Value. This is not fake durability - it's what durability the item given to the player will actually have. This is very important for CustomTexturedItems where the durability is not predetermined, but instead defined upon server startup.

      • setDurability
